  <!--   Chapter  2   -->
  <!--   **********   -->
  <chapter number="2" style="c" sid="ACT 2" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 2:1" />When all the days had been checked off until fifty were reached<char style="sup">[A]</char>—the Day of
        Pentecost—everyone was together and on the same page<char style="sup">[a]</char>. <verse eid="ACT 2:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 2:2" />From out of the sky a noise suddenly occurred, one which seemed like a violent wind was being swept in<char
        style="sup">[b]</char>, and it filled the entire building in which they were sitting. <verse eid="ACT 2:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 2:3" />Tongues like <char style="it">the tongues of the flames </char>from a<char style="it"> </char>fire were
        seen being distributed to them, and <char style="it">a tongue</char> sat upon each and every one of them,<verse eid="ACT 2:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 2:4" />and every one of them was filled with the Holy Spirit and began to speak in various tongues (other languages)
        as the Spirit kept on giving them <char style="it">the unction </char>to be uttering <char style="it">in
        tongues</char>.<verse eid="ACT 2:4" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 2:5" />Now there were Jews staying in Jerusalem, devout men, who were from every nation across the globe<char
        style="sup">[c]</char>. <verse eid="ACT 2:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 2:6" />So when this sound happened, a bunch of them, confused, gathered together, because each person kept hearing
        them speaking in his own dialect of his own language. <verse eid="ACT 2:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 2:7" />They were non-stop confused and kept on wondering saying, “Don’t look <char style="it">now</char>—<char
        style="it">but</char> aren’t all of these folks who are speaking Galileans? <verse eid="ACT 2:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 2:8" />And how <char style="it">is it that</char> each of us <char style="it">can </char>hear <char style="it">what’s
        being spoken</char> in his own native dialect of his own native language?— <verse eid="ACT 2:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 2:9" />Parthians, Medes, Elamites; those who live in Mesopotamia, Judea and not only there but in Cappadocia,
        Pontus, the province of Asia, <verse eid="ACT 2:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 2:10" />Phrygia, and not only there but Pamphylia, Egypt and the parts of Libya around Cyrene; visitors from
        Rome, <verse eid="ACT 2:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 2:11" />both Jews and Gentiles who’ve converted to Judaism; Cretans and Arabs—we all hear them in our own languages
        saying things which magnify God.” <verse eid="ACT 2:11" />
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 2:12" />Now everyone kept on being amazed, confused and perplexed, telling one another, “What in the world’s
        going on<char style="sup">[d]</char>?” <verse eid="ACT 2:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 2:13" />But others, jeering, kept on saying <char style="it">something to the effect</char>, “They <char style="it">went
        off and </char>got drunk on sweet wine<char style="sup">[B]</char>, <char style="it">the stuff the winos
        are always drinking</char>.”<verse eid="ACT 2:13" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 2:14" />Peter along with the eleven others stood <char style="it">to address the crowd</char>, raised his voice,
        and announced, “Men, Judeans<char style="sup">[l]</char>, and everyone who’s staying in Jerusalem: may
        you listen to what I have to say and may this become understood to you. <verse eid="ACT 2:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 2:15" />The fact of the matter is, it’s not what you think, that is that these people are drinking, seeing that
        it’s <char style="it">only </char>nine in the morning, <verse eid="ACT 2:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="ACT 2:16" />but instead this is what’s spoken through the prophet Joel,<verse eid="ACT 2:16" />
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="ACT 2:17" />”’In the Last Days, things will turn out this way,’</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:17">God says:</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:17">‘I’ll pour out My Spirit onto all flesh.</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:17">Your sons and daughters will prophesy,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:17">Your young men will see visions,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:17">Your elderly men will dream dreams.<verse eid="ACT 2:17"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="ACT 2:18" />In those days I will pour out My Spirit</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:18">Upon My male and female servants—</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:18">Indeed I will—</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:18">And they will prophesy.<verse eid="ACT 2:18"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="ACT 2:19" />I will grant that wonders occur in the sky above</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:19">And signs upon the earth below:</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:19">Blood, fire, and smoke trails.<verse eid="ACT 2:19"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="ACT 2:20" />The sun will change into darkness</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:20">And the moon into blood</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:20">Prior to the coming</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:20">Of the Great and Marvelous Day of the Lord.<verse eid="ACT 2:20"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="ACT 2:21" />And things will turn out this way:</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:21">All who choose to call for the Lord <char style="it">to act on his behalf</char></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:21">In the way He is reputed to act<char style="sup">[e]</char></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:21">Will be spared calamity<char style="sup">[f]</char>.’<verse eid="ACT 2:21"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 2:22" />”Men, Israelites<char style="sup">[l]</char>, listen to what I’m telling you. Jesus of Nazareth was a
        man who had been appointed by God to <char style="it">act on </char>our behalf, and God performed miracles,
        wonders, and signs for us through him in your midst, as you all know. <verse eid="ACT 2:22" />
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 2:23" />By the specific determination of God, one which He decided ahead of time, this man was apprehended and
        taken into custody by bad, out-of-control men, fastened to a cross, and <char style="it">the cross was
        </char>hoisted up <char style="it">as a form of execution</char>. <verse eid="ACT 2:23" />
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 2:24" />God resurrected this man, having broken the travail of death, on account of the fact that it wasn’t possible
        for him to be overpowered and constrained by <char style="it">death</char>, <verse eid="ACT 2:24" />
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 2:25" />seeing that <char style="it">in the Scriptures </char>David told him,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:25"></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:25">“Throughout it all, I kept on seeing the Lord ahead of time</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:25">In the area that I was most concerned about<char style="sup">[g]</char></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:25">Because He is right where I need Him<char style="sup">[h]</char></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:25">So that I don’t get rattled.<verse eid="ACT 2:25"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 2:26" />Because of this, I rejoiced in heart and uttered exultations,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:26">And, what’s more, my physical well-being</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:26">Will occupy the spot where hope exists<char style="sup">[i]</char>,<verse eid="ACT 2:26"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="27" style="v" sid="ACT 2:27" />Because You have not left the essence of my life-being</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:27">In the graveyard<char style="sup">[j]</char>,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:27">Nor will You allow your Holy One to undergo decay.<verse eid="ACT 2:27"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="28" style="v" sid="ACT 2:28" />Having familiarized me with the way of life,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:28">You will fill me with gladness</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:28">With Your undivided attention<char style="sup">[k]</char>.<verse eid="ACT 2:28"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="29" style="v" sid="ACT 2:29" />”Men, comrades<char style="sup">[l]</char>, it’s appropriate to address you with confidence concerning
        our patriarch David, <char style="it">to say </char>that he too passed away and was buried, and that
        his tomb has been right nearby <char style="it">from the day he died </char>up until the present time.<verse eid="ACT 2:29" />
      <verse number="30" style="v" sid="ACT 2:30" />So being a prophet and knowing that God made an oath and ‘swore to him that from out of the collection
        of those whom he would sire and their offspring, one of them would sit on his throne,’ <verse eid="ACT 2:30" />
      <verse number="31" style="v" sid="ACT 2:31" />while seeing into the future, he spoke about the resurrection of Jesus; the fact is,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:31"></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:31">“He has neither been left to the graveyard,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:31">Nor has his flesh undergone decay<verse eid="ACT 2:31"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="m">
      <verse number="32" style="v" sid="ACT 2:32" />”God resurrected this Jesus<char style="it">-fellow</char>, of which we all are witnesses, <verse eid="ACT 2:32" />
      <verse number="33" style="v" sid="ACT 2:33" />and thereupon promoted him to the position of God’s Chief Executive<char style="sup">[m]</char>—not only
        that but having received the promise of the Holy Spirit from the Father, he’s poured out <char style="it">all
        of </char>this that you see and hear. <verse eid="ACT 2:33" />
      <verse number="34" style="v" sid="ACT 2:34" />You see, David didn’t ascend into heaven, but it was he specifically who said,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:34"></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:34">“The Lord said to my Lord,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:34">‘Assume the role of being My right-hand man<verse eid="ACT 2:34"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="35" style="v" sid="ACT 2:35" />Until such time I choose</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 2:35">To subjugate your enemies in obeisance to you<char style="sup">[n]</char>’<verse eid="ACT 2:35"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="m">
      <verse number="36" style="v" sid="ACT 2:36" />”Let it be known with certainty to the entire Israeli ethnicity-nation<char style="sup">[o]</char> that
        God made him both Lord and Messiah (Christ), this Jesus-<char style="it">fellow</char> whom you crucified.”<verse eid="ACT 2:36" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="37" style="v" sid="ACT 2:37" />Now, after they heard this, it caused their hearts to melt<char style="sup">[p]</char>, and they told
        Peter and the rest of the apostles, “What should we do about it, men, comrades?” <verse eid="ACT 2:37" />
      <verse number="38" style="v" sid="ACT 2:38" />Peter told<char style="it"> </char>them, “Have a change of heart and of ways<char style="sup">[q]</char>
        and <char style="it">go ahead and</char> have each of you be baptized by the authority of<char style="sup">[r]</char>
        Jesus Christ for the forgiveness of your sins, and you will receive the gift of the Holy Spirit. <verse eid="ACT 2:38" />
      <verse number="39" style="v" sid="ACT 2:39" />You see, the promise is for you, for your children and for everyone who’s far away—it is just as much
        given to the one as to the other<char style="sup">[C]</char>; <char style="it">in other words, </char>it
        is for <char style="it">all </char>those whom the Lord God happens to or chooses to summon.” <verse eid="ACT 2:39" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="40" style="v" sid="ACT 2:40" />He kept on stating<char style="sup">[D]</char> a lot of other declarations, and kept on appealing to
        them <char style="it">summarized by </char>saying, “May you escape<char style="sup">[s]</char> from this
        twisted contemporary Zeitgeist<char style="sup">[t]</char>.” <verse eid="ACT 2:40" />
      <verse number="41" style="v" sid="ACT 2:41" />So those who took to heart and acted upon<char style="sup">[u]</char> his message were baptized, and
        on that day around three-thousand individuals were added. <verse eid="ACT 2:41" />
      <verse number="42" style="v" sid="ACT 2:42" />They were faithful to keep <char style="it">listening to </char>the apostles’ instruction, to keep having
        fellowship-dinners together, dinners culminating in a communion memorial<char style="sup">[v]</char>,
        and to keep attending the prayer meetings.<verse eid="ACT 2:42" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="43" style="v" sid="ACT 2:43" />Now a deep reverence was continually maintained, and many signs and wonders kept on occurring through
        the apostles. <verse eid="ACT 2:43" />
      <verse number="44" style="v" sid="ACT 2:44" />Now all of those believing were on the same page in regard to the previously mentioned things and shared
        everything, <verse eid="ACT 2:44" />
      <verse number="45" style="v" sid="ACT 2:45" />and properties and possessions kept on being sold<char style="sup">[w]</char>, and that which was sold
        kept on being distributed to every person according to whoever happened to have a need<char style="sup">[E]</char>.<verse eid="ACT 2:45" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="46" style="v" sid="ACT 2:46" />Not only that but day by day they continued to be faithful to be in one accord in the temple, and furthermore
        they continued to attend <char style="it">the </char>dinners <char style="it">mentioned previously </char>from
        house to house, sharing food with great joy and simplicity of heart, <verse eid="ACT 2:46" />
      <verse number="47" style="v" sid="ACT 2:47" />praising God and having favor with the entirety of the folk-people—and the Lord kept adding those being
        saved day by day while the previously mentioned things were going on.<verse eid="ACT 2:47" />
    </para>
