  <chapter number="3" style="c" sid="ACT 3" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 3:1" />Now Peter and John went over to the temple at the Three-in-the-Afternoon-Prayer-Time, <verse eid="ACT 3:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 3:2" />and a certain man who was lame from the time he was born, having to be carried around <char style="it">all
        time, </char>was there, whom <char style="it">some people</char> day after day kept on placing at the
        temple gate known as <char style="it">the</char> Beautiful <char style="it">Gate, </char>so that he could
        beg for handouts from those entering the temple <char style="it">complex</char>. <verse eid="ACT 3:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 3:3" />Seeing that Peter and John were about to go into the temple <char style="it">complex</char>, he asked
        for a handout. <verse eid="ACT 3:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 3:4" />Peter stared at him, and John joined in with him, and Peter said, “Look at us!” <verse eid="ACT 3:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 3:5" />He proceeded to give heed to them, looking at them and paying attention to them, waiting to—expecting
        to—get something from them. <verse eid="ACT 3:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 3:6" />Peter said, “I don’t have any cash on me<char style="sup">[A]</char>, but I’ll give you what I’ve got<char
        style="sup">[a]</char>: by the authority vested in me by Jesus Christ of Nazareth<char style="sup">[b]</char>,
        get up and walk around<char style="sup">[B]</char>!”— <verse eid="ACT 3:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 3:7" />And he grabbed him by his right hand and pulled him up—And immediately his feet and ankles were strengthened
        and made sturdy— <verse eid="ACT 3:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 3:8" />And with a leap he stood up and started walking around and entered the temple <char style="it">complex</char>
        together with them, walking around, jumping, and praising God. <verse eid="ACT 3:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 3:9" />All the folk-people saw him walking around and praising God, <verse eid="ACT 3:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 3:10" />and they recognized him as the same beggar who used to<char style="it"> </char>sit <char style="it">where
        the beggars sit </char>at the temple’s Beautiful Gate, and they were filled with amazement and exhilaration
        at how things had turned out for him.<verse eid="ACT 3:10" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 3:11" />While <char style="it">the lame man </char>was clutching Peter and John, folks everywhere<char style="sup">[c]</char>
        at the colonnade known as Solomon’s Colonnade ran towards them, utterly amazed. <verse eid="ACT 3:11" />
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 3:12" />Seeing this, Peter responded to the crowd, “Men, Israelites<char style="sup">[d]</char>, why are you
        amazed at this? Why are you staring at us as though we enabled him to walk by our own power or piety?<verse eid="ACT 3:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 3:13" />The God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob—the God of our patriarchal ancestors—glorified
        His servant<char style="sup">[e]</char> Jesus, whom you all had arrested and whom you all rejected in
        the very presence of Pilate, after that guy delivered a verdict that <char style="it">would have</char>
        set him free. <verse eid="ACT 3:13" />
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 3:14" />You rejected the holy and righteous one and asked for a homicidal man—a murderer—to be let off the hook
        and given back to you. <verse eid="ACT 3:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 3:15" />You killed the Prince of Life, whom God raised from the dead, of which we are witnesses. <verse eid="ACT 3:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="ACT 3:16" />And <char style="it">based </char>on<char style="sup">[f]</char> the faith <char style="it">which is</char>
        <char style="it">derived</char> from <char style="it">Jesus’s </char>authorization to act<char style="sup">[g]</char>,
        this person whom you see and know first-hand—<char style="it">Jesus’s</char> authorization to act strengthened
        <char style="it">him</char> and made <char style="it">him</char> sturdy, and right in front of you all,
        the through-him-faith<char style="sup">[h]</char> gave him this perfect health <char style="it">which
        you see</char>. <verse eid="ACT 3:16" />
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="ACT 3:17" />Yes indeed comrades, I know that you conducted your lives in <char style="it">a way which is</char> consistent
        with ignorance, just like your predecessors and ancestors did, <verse eid="ACT 3:17" />
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="ACT 3:18" />but the God that made the suffering of His Messiah known ahead of time through the mouth of all the prophets
        <char style="it">caused these things be</char> fulfilled in this manner.<verse eid="ACT 3:18" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="ACT 3:19" />”So now, have a change of ways<char style="sup">[i]</char> and turn <char style="it">your hearts</char>
        to the obliteration of your sins, <verse eid="ACT 3:19" />
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="ACT 3:20" />in order that episodes<char style="sup">[j]</char> of refreshing would issue forth from the Lord’s totally-focused
        attention<char style="sup">[k]</char>, and He would send you the one who’s already been appointed <char
        style="it">to a position of authority</char>, Christ Jesus, <verse eid="ACT 3:20" />
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="ACT 3:21" />whom the spiritual world<char style="sup">[l]</char> will most definitely embrace up to the times of
        the establishment of everything that God has spoken through the mouth of His saints—<char style="it">namely</char>
        the prophets—from day-one. <verse eid="ACT 3:21" />
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 3:22" />Yes, <char style="it">in the Old Testament </char>Moses said that,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 3:22"></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 3:22">“The Lord our God will bring to prominence a prophet</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 3:22">And send him your way,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 3:22"><char style="it">A prophet </char>from among our fellow men—</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 3:22"><char style="it">One who is </char>like me.</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 3:22">You shall listen <char style="it">to what comes </char>out of him</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 3:22"><char style="it">And you shall act</char> in accordance to everything</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 3:22">That he happens to say to you.<verse eid="ACT 3:22"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 3:23" />What will happen to any individual</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 3:23">Who chooses not to listen to that prophet</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 3:23">Is that he will be absolutely annihilated,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 3:23">Never seen or heard from again<char style="sup">[m]</char>.<verse eid="ACT 3:23"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 3:24" />”Indeed, all the prophets starting with Samuel, including those who came afterwards, talked about and
        announced these days <char style="it">that</char> <char style="it">we’re living in</char>. <verse eid="ACT 3:24" />
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 3:25" />You all are the beneficiaries<char style="sup">[n]</char> of the prophets and of the covenant which God
        entered into with our ancestors, saying to Abraham, ‘All of the nationalities<char style="sup">[o]</char>
        of the earth will be blessed by one of your descendants<char style="sup">[p]</char>.’ <verse eid="ACT 3:25" />
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 3:26" />God first and foremost brought to prominence his servant<char style="sup">[e]</char> and sent him your
        way blessing you when each person turns away from your evil ways.”<verse eid="ACT 3:26" />
    </para>
