  <chapter number="6" style="c" sid="ACT 6" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 6:1" />Now during this timeframe when the number of disciples was expanding, a complaint originated from the
        Greek-speaking Jews against the native Israeli Jews, that their widows<char style="sup">[A]</char> were
        being overlooked in the Daily <char style="it">Meal </char>Service. <verse eid="ACT 6:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 6:2" />So the twelve summoned the bulk of the disciples and said, “We’re not happy about neglecting the teaching
        of God’s word by being restaurant waiters<char style="sup">[a]</char>. <verse eid="ACT 6:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 6:3" />Look into <char style="it">the matter</char>, comrades, <char style="it">and come up with</char> seven
        men from among you that it’s been observed<char style="sup">[b]</char> <char style="it">and generally
        agreed </char>are full of spirit<char style="sup">[B]</char> and wisdom, whom we might put in charge
        of this matter<char style="sup">[C]</char>. <verse eid="ACT 6:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 6:4" />We, though, will devote ourselves to prayer and to the ministry of the word <char style="it">of God</char>.”<verse eid="ACT 6:4" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 6:5" />The reasoning put forth was agreeable in the view of the large group assembled, and Stephen, a man full
        of faith and the Holy Spirit, Philip, Procorus, Nicanor, Timon, Parmenas, and Nicolas, who was a convert
        to Judaism from Antioch, were chosen. <verse eid="ACT 6:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 6:6" />They stood <char style="it">these men </char>before the apostles, and after they prayed for them, they
        laid <char style="it">their </char>hands on them. <verse eid="ACT 6:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 6:7" />And the word of God kept on being proclaimed, being received, and producing results<char style="sup">[c]</char>,
        and the number of disciples in Jerusalem continued to grow at a high rate, and a bunch of the priests
        began to obey <char style="it">by believing </char>in the faith.<verse eid="ACT 6:7" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 6:8" />Now Stephen, full of grace—God’s favor and His willingness to work through him—and miracle-working capability,
        began to perform tremendous miracles<char style="sup">[d]</char> among the people. <verse eid="ACT 6:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 6:9" />Some people from the synagogue of those who are said to be Freedmen, Cyrenians, Alexandrians, and those
        from Cilicia and <char style="it">the Roman Province of </char>Asia asserted themselves, arguing with
        Stephen, <verse eid="ACT 6:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 6:10" />and didn’t have the strength <char style="it">of words </char>to withstand the wisdom and the spirit
        with which he continuously spoke. <verse eid="ACT 6:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 6:11" />Then they got men to claim that, “While he was speaking, we <char style="it">definitely</char> heard
        him make a blasphemous remark against the Bible<char style="sup">[e]</char> and God,” <verse eid="ACT 6:11" />
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 6:12" />and stirred up the folk-people, the councilmen, and the designated teachers<char style="sup">[f]</char>
        and descended on him all of a sudden, apprehended him, and brought him into the Council <char style="it">chamber.</char><verse eid="ACT 6:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 6:13" />From there, the phony witnesses produced testimony saying, “This man won’t stop uttering remarks against
        this Holy Place and the Bible<char style="sup">[e]</char><char style="it">. </char><verse eid="ACT 6:13" />
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 6:14" />The fact is, we <char style="it">definitely</char> heard him saying that this Jesus-of-Nazareth-<char
        style="it">guy </char>will destroy this place and alter the traditions which Moses passed down to us.”<verse eid="ACT 6:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 6:15" />The panel of councilmen fixed their eyes upon him and looked at his face and saw that his countenance
        was like the countenance of an angel.<verse eid="ACT 6:15" />
    </para>
