  <chapter number="8" style="c" sid="ACT 8" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 8:1" />Now Saul whole-heartedly agreed with eliminating <char style="it">Stephen</char>.</para>
    <para style="p" vid="ACT 8:1">On that day a terrible persecution broke out against the church—the gathering <char style="it">of believers</char>—in
        Jerusalem. Everyone scattered over the Judean and Samarian countryside except for the apostles. <verse eid="ACT 8:1"/>
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 8:2" />Devout men buried Stephen and mourned greatly for him during the period of mourning held for him. <verse eid="ACT 8:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 8:3" />Saul proceeded to go from house to house ravaging the church, barging in<char style="sup">[a]</char>
        and dragging off men and women, arresting them and putting them in jail.<verse eid="ACT 8:3" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 8:4" />Those who were scattering <char style="it">throughout the countryside </char>were announcing the good
        news message—proclaiming the Gospel, the good news of the Word. <verse eid="ACT 8:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 8:5" />Philip went over to a Samaritan city and proceeded to preach Christ to them. <verse eid="ACT 8:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 8:6" />The crowds eagerly took in the various statements made by Philip, united in one heart and mind in their
        listening and in their watching miracles that he performed. <verse eid="ACT 8:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 8:7" />The fact is, many filthy, disgusting spirits were being cast out<char style="sup">[b]</char> one after
        another, crying out in a loud voice <char style="it">as they left</char>. Many paralyzed and lame were
        being healed. <verse eid="ACT 8:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 8:8" />Much joy took place in that city.<verse eid="ACT 8:8" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 8:9" />Now a certain man named Simon used to awe the Samaritans in the city by practicing magic, claiming to
        be someone special<char style="sup">[c]</char>, <verse eid="ACT 8:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 8:10" />a person who captivated everyone’s attention, from the insignificant to the important, what they were
        describing as, “God’s miracle-working power: the Bomb.<char style="sup">[d]</char>” <verse eid="ACT 8:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 8:11" />They kept paying attention to him for a long time, dazzled by the works of magic. <verse eid="ACT 8:11" />
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 8:12" />But when they believed Philip proclaiming the good news of God’s kingdom and proclaiming the authority
        vested in Jesus Christ and what he’s all about<char style="sup">[e]</char>, they proceeded to be baptized,
        men and women both. <verse eid="ACT 8:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 8:13" />Simon himself also believed and, once baptized, while sticking like glue to<char style="sup">[f]</char>
        Philip and seeing spectacular miracles<char style="sup">[g]</char> and tremendous miracle-working abilities,
        kept on becoming more and more enchanted by having been dazzled over and over again.<verse eid="ACT 8:13" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 8:14" />Now once the apostles in Jerusalem heard that Samaria had whole-heartedly embraced and acted upon<char
        style="sup">[h]</char> God’s word, they sent them Peter and John, <verse eid="ACT 8:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 8:15" />such individuals who<char style="sup">[i]</char> would go over and pray for them so that they would receive
        <char style="it">the</char> Holy Spirit<char style="sup">[A]</char>: <verse eid="ACT 8:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="ACT 8:16" />for he (<char style="it">the Holy Spirit) </char>had not yet fallen<char style="sup">[B]</char> upon
        any one of them, but they only existed in a state where they had been baptized<char style="sup">[C]</char>
        into all that the Lord Jesus stands for<char style="sup">[j]</char>. <verse eid="ACT 8:16" />
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="ACT 8:17" />Then they laid hands on them and they began receiving the Holy Spirit. <verse eid="ACT 8:17" />
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="ACT 8:18" />Simon, seeing the Spirit given through the apostles’ laying on of hands, offered them money <verse eid="ACT 8:18" />
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="ACT 8:19" />saying,</para>
    <para style="p" vid="ACT 8:19">“Give me this ability too, so that the person I lay my hands on<char style="it"> </char>would receive
        the Holy Spirit.”<verse eid="ACT 8:19"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="ACT 8:20" />But Peter said to him, “Get lost—I hope you die—you and your money along with you<char style="sup">[k]</char>—since
        you assumed you could acquire God’s offering<char style="sup">[D]</char> <char style="it">to mankind</char>
        through cash. <verse eid="ACT 8:20" />
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="ACT 8:21" />You don’t get to participate in this business—not even a bit<char style="sup">[l]</char>, seeing that
        your heart is not right in God’s sight<char style="sup">[m]</char>. <verse eid="ACT 8:21" />
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 8:22" />So abandon<char style="sup">[n]</char> this wickedness and beg the Lord if he would somehow possibly
        forgive your heart’s intention; <verse eid="ACT 8:22" />
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 8:23" />the fact is, I see that you’re coughing up bitterness and are handcuffed by unrighteousness.”<verse eid="ACT 8:23" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 8:24" />In response, Simon said, “You all pray to the Lord on my behalf, so that I won’t be afflicted by what
        you’ve said<char style="sup">[o]</char>.”<verse eid="ACT 8:24" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 8:25" />So then they thoroughly presented and spoke about the concept of the Lord and returned to Jerusalem,
        and many Samaritan towns began to have the good news proclaimed in them.<verse eid="ACT 8:25" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 8:26" />Now an angel spoke to Philip, “Head on out south on the road which runs from Jerusalem to Gaza, the one
        that nobody uses.” <verse eid="ACT 8:26" />
      <verse number="27" style="v" sid="ACT 8:27" />He got going. Out of nowhere an Ethiopian man appeared, a eunuch who had control over the Queen of Ethiopia’s
        entire treasury, one who had gone to Jerusalem to worship <verse eid="ACT 8:27" />
      <verse number="28" style="v" sid="ACT 8:28" />and was on the return trip sitting on his chariot and reading out of the prophet Isaiah. <verse eid="ACT 8:28" />
      <verse number="29" style="v" sid="ACT 8:29" />The Spirit said to Philip, “Go up to him and join his chariot.” <verse eid="ACT 8:29" />
      <verse number="30" style="v" sid="ACT 8:30" />Philip ran over to him and heard him reading<char style="sup">[E]</char> out of the prophet Isaiah, and
        said, “Hmm…do you really understand what you’re reading?” <verse eid="ACT 8:30" />
      <verse number="31" style="v" sid="ACT 8:31" />He said, “Ya, about that. How would I be able to unless someone walks me through it?”, and he asked Philip
        to climb aboard the chariot, sit down together with him, and help him out. <verse eid="ACT 8:31" />
      <verse number="32" style="v" sid="ACT 8:32" />The passage of Scripture which he was in the middle of reading was this:</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 8:32"></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 8:32">Like a sheep led to slaughter</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 8:32">And like a lamb speechless before the shearer:</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 8:32">In the same way he won’t open his mouth.<verse eid="ACT 8:32"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="33" style="v" sid="ACT 8:33" />In his self-abasement his justice has been stripped <char style="it">from him.</char></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 8:33">How can anyone <char style="it">possibly</char> describe</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 8:33">The prevailing Zeitgeist of his time<char style="sup">[p]</char>,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 8:33">Since his life has been wiped off the face of the Earth<char style="sup">[q]</char>?<verse eid="ACT 8:33"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="34" style="v" sid="ACT 8:34" />Upon reflection the eunuch said to Philip, “Can I ask you whom the prophet’s talking about here? Is he
        talking about himself or about someone else?” <verse eid="ACT 8:34" />
      <verse number="35" style="v" sid="ACT 8:35" />Philip opened his mouth and, from this passage of Scripture, began to tell him all about the good news
        of Jesus. <verse eid="ACT 8:35" />
      <verse number="36" style="v" sid="ACT 8:36" />As they were going down the road, they stumbled across some water, and the eunuch said, “Look—water:
        what’s stopping me from getting baptized?” <verse eid="ACT 8:36" />
      <verse number="37" style="v" sid="ACT 8:37" /><char style="sup">[F]</char> <verse eid="ACT 8:37" />
      <verse number="38" style="v" sid="ACT 8:38" />He ordered his chariot to come to a halt, and both of them—Philip and the eunuch—got off <char style="it">the
        chariot </char>and went into the water, and <char style="it">Philip</char> baptized him. <verse eid="ACT 8:38" />
      <verse number="39" style="v" sid="ACT 8:39" />When they got out of the water, the Spirit of the Lord took hold of Philip and redirected him<char style="sup">[r]</char>,
        and the eunuch didn’t see him anymore; you see, he was going his way rejoicing. <verse eid="ACT 8:39" />
      <verse number="40" style="v" sid="ACT 8:40" />Philip wound up in Azotus, and while travelling through there kept on proclaiming the good news to all
        of the cities all the way to Caesarea.<verse eid="ACT 8:40" />
    </para>
