  <!--   **********   -->
  <chapter number="11" style="c" sid="ACT 11" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 11:1" />Now the apostles and comrades<char style="sup">[a]</char> over in Judea heard that the Gentiles too <char
        style="it">and not just the Jews </char>had whole-heartedly embraced and acted upon<char style="sup">[b]</char>
        God&apos;s word, God’s system of logic. <verse eid="ACT 11:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 11:2" />When Peter went over to Jerusalem, <char style="it">the believers</char> who adhered to Judaism strictly<char
        style="sup">[c]</char> proceeded to show that they had misgivings about what he did and questioned what
        he did: <verse eid="ACT 11:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 11:3" />“You went into <char style="it">a house </char>that has those outside of Judaism<char style="sup">[d]</char>
        <char style="it">in it </char>and shared a meal with them.”<verse eid="ACT 11:3" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 11:4" />Peter proceeded to explain to them <char style="it">what happened</char>, explaining it in sequential
        order: <verse eid="ACT 11:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 11:5" />“I was in Joppa praying and had a vision <char style="it">while</char> in a trance: <char style="it">the
        vision was of </char>an object something like a huge, four-cornered cloth sheet descending out of the
        sky, and it came as far as me and stopped. <verse eid="ACT 11:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 11:6" />I stared at it and started to notice <char style="it">what was there</char>: I saw the <char style="it">gamut
        of</char> four-footed animals, wild beasts, reptiles, and birds from the sky. <verse eid="ACT 11:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 11:7" />Along with it, I heard a voice telling me, ‘Get to it, Peter: slaughter and eat <char style="it">them.</char>’<verse eid="ACT 11:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 11:8" />But I said, ‘No way, sir, since nothing which isn’t kosher has ever entered my mouth.’ <verse eid="ACT 11:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 11:9" />A second time a voice from the sky spoke in reply, ‘That which God has purged of its non-kosher-ness
        is <char style="it">permissible for</char> you <char style="it">to eat</char>.’ <verse eid="ACT 11:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 11:10" />This happened a third time, and <char style="it">the objects in the vision</char> were taken back up
        into the sky again. <verse eid="ACT 11:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 11:11" />Just like that, three men stopped at the house which I was <char style="it">staying, </char>men sent
        as messengers<char style="sup">[A]</char> from Cornelius to me. <verse eid="ACT 11:11" />
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 11:12" />The Spirit told me to have no doubts or reservations and go introduce myself to them. Some of the comrades—these
        fellows <char style="it">here</char>—also accompanied me, and we entered the man’s house.<verse eid="ACT 11:12" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 11:13" />”He reported how he saw an angel in his house, and the angel stood there and said, ‘Send messengers to
        Joppa and send for Simon who goes by Peter, <verse eid="ACT 11:13" />
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 11:14" />who’ll speak to you and tell you things by which you will be rescued from your spiritual malaise<char
        style="sup">[e]</char>, you and your entire household<char style="sup">[B]</char>.’ <verse eid="ACT 11:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 11:15" />While I was just getting started talking, the <char style="it">baptism in the</char> Holy Spirit fell
        on them just like it did on us too way-back-when. <verse eid="ACT 11:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="ACT 11:16" />But I remembered the Lord’s sayings, as he kept on telling us, <char style="wj">‘Sure, John baptized
        with water, but you all will be baptized with the Holy Spirit.’</char> <verse eid="ACT 11:16" />
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="ACT 11:17" />So now, if God gave the same exact offering—gift—to them as He gave to us too, to believe in<char style="sup">[f]</char>
        the Lord Jesus Christ, who was I to stand in God’s way<char style="sup">[g]</char>?” <verse eid="ACT 11:17" />
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="ACT 11:18" />After hearing this, they fell silent and glorified God saying, “Then <char style="it">that means that
        </char>God also granted the Gentiles the Complete-Changeover which leads to<char style="sup">[h]</char>
        <char style="it">that special fullness of </char>life.”<verse eid="ACT 11:18" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="ACT 11:19" />So now, those who were scattered because of the pressure due to the persecution that occurred upon Stephen’s
        <char style="it">stoning </char>spread out as far as Phoenicia, Cyprus, and Antioch telling the Concept
        to Jews alone. <verse eid="ACT 11:19" />
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="ACT 11:20" />Among them were some men from Cyprus and Cyrene, men in particular who went to Antioch and were talking
        and talking to the Greek-speaking Jews, telling them the good news—the Gospel—of the Lord Jesus. <verse eid="ACT 11:20" />
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="ACT 11:21" />The Lord was supernaturally and spectacularly working behind the scenes in conjunction with them<char
        style="sup">[i]</char>, and <char style="it">consequently </char>there were many people who believed
        and turned to the Lord.<verse eid="ACT 11:21" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 11:22" />The whole story was heard by the ears of the church in Jerusalem, and they dispatched Barnabas, who <char
        style="it">passed </char>through <char style="it">the region </char>until he got to Antioch. <verse eid="ACT 11:22" />
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 11:23" />Once he got there and got to see <char style="it">the manifestation of </char>God’s grace, rejoiced.
        Because he was a good man, full of the Holy Spirit, and faithful, he advised, encouraged, and in every
        way helped<char style="sup">[C]</char> them all with a heartfelt determination to stick with it until
        the Lord comes <char style="it">back</char>. <verse eid="ACT 11:23" />
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 11:24" /><char style="sup">[j]</char> —And a good-many people were added to the Lord. <verse eid="ACT 11:24" />
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 11:25" />He left for Tarsus to hunt Saul down, <verse eid="ACT 11:25" />
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 11:26" />and once he found him brought him to Antioch. As things turned out in their case, they got together in
        the church for a whole year and taught a good number of people, and <char style="it">as a result </char>the
        disciples were first referred to as “Christians<char style="sup">[D]</char>” in Antioch.<verse eid="ACT 11:26" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="27" style="v" sid="ACT 11:27" />During this timeframe, prophets went from Jerusalem to Antioch. <verse eid="ACT 11:27" />
      <verse number="28" style="v" sid="ACT 11:28" />One of them by the name of Agabus stood up and through the Spirit portended that a huge famine over the
        entire civilized world<char style="sup">[E]</char>was going to occur, which happened during <char style="it">the
        Roman Emperor</char> Claudius’s <char style="it">reign</char>. <verse eid="ACT 11:28" />
      <verse number="29" style="v" sid="ACT 11:29" />The disciples <char style="it">reacted in such a way</char> that what came out of them was that each
        one of them, as far as he had the means to do so, determined to send a ministry<char style="it">-gift</char>
        to the comrades living in Judea. <verse eid="ACT 11:29" />
      <verse number="30" style="v" sid="ACT 11:30" />They did <char style="it">just that</char> and sent <char style="it">the money they collected </char>to
        the presiding board, <char style="it">the leaders of the church in Jerusalem</char><char style="sup">[F]</char>,
        using Barnabas and Saul as couriers<char style="sup">[k]</char>.<verse eid="ACT 11:30" />
    </para>
