  <!--   **********   -->
  <chapter number="15" style="c" sid="ACT 15" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 15:1" />A few key people came over from Judea and proceeded to tell them how things ought to be done, instructing<char
        style="sup">[A]</char> the comrades<char style="sup">[a]</char> that you’ve got to be circumcised in
        Moses (<char style="it">i.e. become Jewish and commit to obeying the commandments in the Law of Moses</char>),
        or else you can’t be saved (<char style="it">i.e. receive Christ and walk with him</char>). <verse eid="ACT 15:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 15:2" />No small disagreement and debate occurred between Paul and Barnabas on one side and them on the other,
        and they arranged for Paul, Barnabas, and certain others from among them to go to the apostles and the
        presiding board<char style="sup">[b]</char> in Jerusalem in regard to this debate. <verse eid="ACT 15:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 15:3" />So then those sent forth by the church kept creating tremendous joy among the comrades as they were passing
        through Phoenicia and Samaria recounting the Gentiles’ conversion. <verse eid="ACT 15:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 15:4" />Arriving in Jerusalem, they were welcomed by the church, the apostles, and the presiding board, and reported
        what God was doing in conjunction with them.<verse eid="ACT 15:4" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 15:5" />Now a few who belonged to the Pharisee-sect and who had become believers stood up to speak and said that
        <char style="it">the Gentile believers</char> must be circumcised (<char style="it">and thus convert
        to Judaism</char>) and be ordered to adhere to the Law of Moses, <verse eid="ACT 15:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 15:6" />and the apostles and the presiding board got together to look into this matter. <verse eid="ACT 15:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 15:7" />After much debate took place, Peter stood up and told them:</para>
    <para style="p" vid="ACT 15:7">“Men, comrades: you understand that from the very start (our start that is), God chose that the Gentiles
        hear the Gospel through my mouth and become believers. <verse eid="ACT 15:7"/>
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 15:8" />God, the Knower-Of-The-Heart, went on record and told them that He would give them the <char style="it">baptism
        of the </char>Holy Spirit just like He gave it to us. <verse eid="ACT 15:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 15:9" />After their hearts were cleansed by faith, no one discriminated against them<char style="sup">[c]</char>.<verse eid="ACT 15:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 15:10" />So at this point in time, you’re trying God’s patience (testing God) by placing an <char style="it">unnecessary</char>
        burden on the disciples (putting a yoke on the disciples’ necks), one which neither our ancestors nor
        we were strong enough to bear. <verse eid="ACT 15:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 15:11" />No—<char style="it">it’s </char>through the grace of the Lord Jesus that one exercises faith to be saved
        <char style="it">from their sin</char> following the same pattern as those people did.”<verse eid="ACT 15:11" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 15:12" />The whole lot of them fell silent and began to listen to Barnabas and Paul explain the miracles<char
        style="sup">[d]</char> that God did among the Gentiles through them. <verse eid="ACT 15:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 15:13" />After their silence, James<char style="sup">[B]</char> responded, “Men, comrades, listen to me. <verse eid="ACT 15:13" />
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 15:14" />Simon explained the way that, for the first time, God paid a visit—a caring, helping type of visit—in
        order to form a <char style="it">unique group of </char>people from out of the Gentiles, a people consecrated
        to everything He represents<char style="sup">[C]</char>. <verse eid="ACT 15:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 15:15" />The words of the prophets agree with this, as it’s written:<verse eid="ACT 15:15" />
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="ACT 15:16" />”’After this <char style="it">occurs,</char> I will return</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 15:16">And rebuild David’s fallen condo<char style="sup">[e]</char></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 15:16">And rebuild what remains of it</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 15:16">And restore it,<verse eid="ACT 15:16"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="ACT 15:17" />So that what’s left of the people</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 15:17"><char style="it">Just </char>might seek out the Lord,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 15:17">Plus all of the Gentiles upon whom</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 15:17">My mark of ownership<char style="sup">[f]</char> was assigned to,’</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="ACT 15:17">Says the Lord who’s doing this<verse eid="ACT 15:17"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="ACT 15:18" /><char style="it">and</char> <char style="it">Who’s been making this</char> known from eternity <char
        style="it">past</char><char style="sup">[g]</char><char style="it">.</char><verse eid="ACT 15:18" />
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="m">
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="ACT 15:19" />”Therefore I decided not to bother those who are of Gentile origin who are turning to God, <verse eid="ACT 15:19" />
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="ACT 15:20" />but instead to write them letters <char style="it">which tell them</char> to abstain <char style="it">from</char>
        <char style="it">the detestable things forbidden by of the Law of Moses</char>: from things polluted
        by idols, from <char style="it">bizarre</char> sexual immorality<char style="sup">[D]</char>, and from
        <char style="it">drinking the </char>blood remaining in the body <char style="it">of an animal after
        it’s been </char>killed by having its neck broken<char style="sup">[E]</char>. <verse eid="ACT 15:20" />
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="ACT 15:21" />You see, going back to ancient times, <char style="it">the Law of </char>Moses has <char style="it">always
        had </char>those who preach it, as it’s being read aloud in the synagogues in city after city, Sabbath
        after Sabbath.”<verse eid="ACT 15:21" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 15:22" />Then the apostles and the presiding board in conjunction with the entire church decided what was best
        to do<char style="sup">[h]</char> and chose men from among them to send with Paul and Barnabas to Antioch,
        <char style="it">namely</char> Judas, who goes by Barsabbas, and Silas, men who were leaders among <char
        style="it">their</char> comrades, <verse eid="ACT 15:22" />
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 15:23" />and wrote a certified letter so there would be no doubt of its authenticity<char style="sup">[F]</char>,</para>
    <para style="p" vid="ACT 15:23">“The apostles and the presiding board, comrades: to the comrades up and down Antioch, Syria, and Cilicia,
        those who are of Gentile origin. Greetings<char style="sup">[i]</char>! <verse eid="ACT 15:23"/>
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 15:24" />Because we heard that some of our own people have <char style="it">of their own initiative </char>ventured
        out and troubled you with remarks unsettling to your mind<char style="sup">[j]</char>, people who have
        not been issued instructions <char style="it">to do so</char>, <verse eid="ACT 15:24" />
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 15:25" />all of us were in agreement in deciding what was best to do and chose comrades to send you who will accompany
        our beloved Barnabas and Paul, <verse eid="ACT 15:25" />
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 15:26" />men who have dedicated their lives to<char style="sup">[k]</char> to all that our Lord Jesus Christ stands
        for<char style="sup">[l]</char>. <verse eid="ACT 15:26" />
      <verse number="27" style="v" sid="ACT 15:27" />So we have sent Judas and Silas, and they will report the same <char style="it">as what is written here
        </char>through word-of-mouth. <verse eid="ACT 15:27" />
      <verse number="28" style="v" sid="ACT 15:28" />The fact is, the Holy Spirit and we thought it best not to make you shoulder any more burden<char style="sup">[m]</char>
        than these <char style="it">items</char> <char style="it">which we’re listing here</char>, which are
        <char style="it">absolutely</char> necessary: <verse eid="ACT 15:28" />
      <verse number="29" style="v" sid="ACT 15:29" />abstain from food sacrificed to idols, from slaughtering an animal with the intent of drinking its blood,
        and from <char style="it">bizarre</char> sexual immorality.”<verse eid="ACT 15:29" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="30" style="v" sid="ACT 15:30" />So then, once they were released<char style="sup">[G]</char>, they went up to Antioch, gathered the community
        <char style="it">of believers </char>together<char style="it">, </char>and gave <char style="it">them
        </char>the letter. <verse eid="ACT 15:30" />
      <verse number="31" style="v" sid="ACT 15:31" />After it was read they rejoiced at the advice, exhortation, and encouragement. <verse eid="ACT 15:31" />
      <verse number="32" style="v" sid="ACT 15:32" />Judas and Silas as well exhorted and encouraged the comrades by means of many short <char style="it">prophetic</char>
        messages<char style="sup">[n]</char> (they being prophets in their own right) and put them on a firm
        footing<char style="sup">[o]</char>. <verse eid="ACT 15:32" />
      <verse number="33" style="v" sid="ACT 15:33" />After putting in time there, they were released<char style="sup">[G]</char> in good standing<char style="sup">[H]</char>
        from the comrades <char style="it">back </char>to the ones who sent them.<verse eid="ACT 15:33" />
      <verse number="34" style="v" sid="ACT 15:34" /><char style="sup">[I]</char> <verse eid="ACT 15:34" />
      <verse number="35" style="v" sid="ACT 15:35" />Paul and Barnabas continued on in Antioch teaching and evangelizing the Word of the Lord, and many others
        did too.<verse eid="ACT 15:35" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="36" style="v" sid="ACT 15:36" />After some days Paul said to Barnabas, “Let’s return to the cities in which we proclaimed the word of
        the Lord and go from city to city visiting the comrades there and see how they’re getting on <char style="it">in
        their faith</char>.” <verse eid="ACT 15:36" />
      <verse number="37" style="v" sid="ACT 15:37" />Now Barnabas was wanting to take Mark (i.e. John who goes by Mark) along with them too, <verse eid="ACT 15:37" />
      <verse number="38" style="v" sid="ACT 15:38" />but Paul was thinking it fitting not to take Mark along, the guy who deserted them, leaving them at Pamphylia
        and ceasing to accompany them on their mission. <verse eid="ACT 15:38" />
      <verse number="39" style="v" sid="ACT 15:39" />A sharp disagreement took place to the point where they parted ways from each other, and Barnabas took
        Mark and sailed for Cyprus. <verse eid="ACT 15:39" />
      <verse number="40" style="v" sid="ACT 15:40" />Paul called on Silas <char style="it">to accompany him</char> and left, after being handed over to the
        Lord’s grace <char style="it">for safe keeping </char>by the comrades. <verse eid="ACT 15:40" />
      <verse number="41" style="v" sid="ACT 15:41" />He went on and on passing through Syria putting the churches on a firm footing<char style="sup">[o]</char>.<verse eid="ACT 15:41" />
    </para>
