    <note caller="[A]" style="f">
      <char style="fk">[A]</char>
      <char style="ft"><char style="it">Some of the Epicurean and Stoic philosophers</char>…Or: <char style="it">certain Epicurean
        and Stoic philosophers</char>. In the GT for, Luke is explicit in saying that the philosophers here were
        only Epicurean and Stoic, and no other kinds. As the two schools of philosophy, stoicism and epicureanism,
        have debated each other since their inception, Luke is insinuating that they’re wanting to see how Paul
        and his teaching fit into the framework of the stoicism vs. epicureanism debate.</char>
    </note>
    <note caller="[B]" style="f">
      <char style="fk">[B]</char>
      <char style="ft"><char style="it">What point is this dilettante-intellectual here trying to make</char>?…Lit: <char style="it">What
