    <note caller="[c]" style="f">
      <char style="fk">[c]</char>
      <char style="ft"><char style="it">hit you back</char>…Lit: <char style="it">be striking you</char>. The Gk. verb tense
        used in the word <char style="it">hit </char>insinuates an open-ended retaliation rather than a tit-for-tat
        retaliation.</char>
    </note>
    <note caller="[d]" style="f">
      <char style="fk">[d]</char>
      <char style="ft"><char style="it">bogus judge</char>…Lit: <char style="it">whitewashed wall</char>. Liberties taken. A
        commonly-used idiom used in Israel at that time. Ref. Matt. 23:27, Luke 11:44.</char>
    </note>
