    <note caller="[i]" style="f">
      <char style="fk">[i]</char>
      <char style="ft"><char style="it">swearing that we would be cursed if we break it</char>…In Gk. reads <char style="it">anathemati
        anethematisamev </char>(Ἀναθέματι ἀνεθεματίσαμεν), <char style="w" strong="G00332">Ἀναθέματι</char>),
        <char style="w" strong="G00331">ἀνεθεματίσαμεν</char>), which shares the same root as the word <char
        style="it">anathema; </char>and the words are repeated as a figure of speech.</char>
      <char style="fp"></char>
