      <char style="ft"><char style="it">for the Jews to owe him a favor</char>…Lit: <char style="it">a favor to lay down with
        the Jews</char>. This is expression is also used in Acts 25:9. The exchange of favors was part what maintained
        the delicate political equilibrium between the Romans and the Jews.</char>
